                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>N York</placeName>, <date>Nov 2.\n                5621/1860</date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir—</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\"><sic>Inclosed</sic> the continuation<lb/> of the “Declaration of\n                Independence.” I<lb/> thought the portion sent to you at first,<lb/> was enough for\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">two</hi> weeks, as I<lb/> wish to spin out the publication till<lb/>\n                <date>Chanukah</date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your correspondent “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                        ><persName>Counsellor</persName></hi>” deals<lb/> in contemptible duplicity.\n                He says: “<persName>Rev.<lb/> Dr Fishel</persName> &amp;c &amp;c.” (page 189, col.\n                3) What<lb/> is the truth? 104 votes were cast, of<lb/> these\n                    <persName>F.</persName> received 53, that is to say, he<lb/> was reelected by a\n                majority of two<lb/> votes. If he had yet one spark of<lb/> pride and principle left\n                in him, he<lb/> would have respectfully declined; but<lb/> no, even because half of\n                the congregati<lb/>on do not want him, he will take<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">their</hi> money and they <hi rend=\"underline\">must</hi> listen\n                to<lb/> him, or he will receive <del>their</del> insult<lb/> offered to him by their\n                leaving the Syna-</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3028q03v/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
